尽管[[火星|火星]]拥有[[火星極冠|冰盖]]且[[太陽系外行星|其他行星]]可能拥有海洋<ref>Ravilious, Kate. "[http://news.nationalgeographic.co.uk/news/2009/04/090421-most-earthlike-planet.html Most Earthlike Planet Yet Found May Have Liquid Oceans] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130921053256/http://news.nationalgeographic.co.uk/news/2009/04/090421-most-earthlike-planet.html |date=2013-09-21 }}" in ''National Geographic''. 21 Apr 2009. Accessed 10 Sept 2013.</ref>，但[[地球|地球]]是已知唯一表面由[[液态水|液态水]]覆盖的[[行星|行星]]<ref name=Stow>{{cite book|ref=Stow | title=Encyclopedia of the Oceans | publisher=Oxford University Press | author=Stow, Dorrik | year=2004 | isbn=0-19-860687-7}}</ref>{{rp|page=22}}。地球上的水的来源尚不明确。从[[太空|太空]]遥望，地球像是一顆“[[藍色彈珠|藍色彈珠]]”，水以海洋、[[冰盖|冰盖]]和[[云|云层]]等不同形態存在。<ref>Platnick, Steven. "[http://visibleearth.nasa.gov/view.php?id=57723 Visible Earth] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130426033107/http://visibleearth.nasa.gov/view.php?id=57723 |date=2013-04-26 }}". [[National_Aeronautics_and_Space_Administration|NASA]]. Accessed 22 Apr 2013.</ref>地球上海水體積為{{convert|1,335,000,000|km3|mi3|sp=us}}，佔地球{{tsl|en|Water distribution on Earth|地球水資源分布|水资源约97.2%}}<ref name=NOAAcycle/>{{efn|Hydrous [[尖晶橄榄石|ringwoodite]] recovered from [[火山噴發類型|volcanic eruptions]] suggests that the mantle transition zone between the [[地幔|lower]] and [[地幔|upper mantle]] holds between one<ref>Oskin, Becky. [http://www.scientificamerican.com/article/rare-diamond-confirms-that-earths-mantle-holds-an-oceans-worth-of-water/ "Rare Diamond Confirms that Earth's Mantle Holds an Ocean's Worth of Water"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140313123135/http://www.scientificamerican.com/article/rare-diamond-confirms-that-earths-mantle-holds-an-oceans-worth-of-water/ |date=2014-03-13 }} in ''[[科学美国人|Scientific American]]''. 12 Mar 2014. Accessed 13 Mar 2014.</ref> and three<ref>Schmandt, Brandon & al. [http://www.sciencemag.org/content/344/6189/1265 "Dehydration Melting at the Top of the Lower Mantle"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140616031401/http://www.sciencemag.org/content/344/6189/1265 |date=2014-06-16 }} in ''Science'', {{nowrap|Vol. 344}}, {{nowrap|No. 6189}}, {{nowrap|pp. 1265–68}}. 13 Jun 2014. DOI 10.1126/science.1253358. Accessed 13 Jun 2014.</ref> times as much water as all of the world's surface oceans combined. Experiments to recreate the conditions of the lower mantle suggest it may contain still more water as well, as much as five times the mass of water present in the world's oceans.<ref>Harder, Ben. "[http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2002/03/0307_0307_waterworld.html Inner Earth May Hold More Water Than the Seas] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140327131235/http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2002/03/0307_0307_waterworld.html |date=2014-03-27 }}" in ''[[国家地理_(杂志)|National Geographic]]''. 7 Mar 2002. Accessed 14 Nov 2013.</ref><ref>Murakami, Motohiko & al. "[http://www.sciencemag.org/content/295/5561/1885.short Water in Earth's Lower Mantle] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924150204/http://www.sciencemag.org/content/295/5561/1885.short |date=2015-09-24 }}" in ''Science'', {{nowrap|Vol. 295}}, {{nowrap|No. 5561}}, {{nowrap|pp. 1885–87}}. 8 Mar 2002. Accessed 8 Aug 2014.</ref>}}並覆盖着地球70％以上的表面<ref name=Stow />{{rp|page=7}}，另有约2.15%的地球水資源以冰的形式存在，分布於[[北冰洋|北冰洋]]海冰、[[南极洲|南极洲]]冰冠和[[南冰洋|南冰洋]]海冰，以及世界各地的[[冰川|冰川]]和表层沉积物中。其余约0.65％的水資源组成了[[地下水|地下水]]或处在水循环的各个阶段，包括人们在生活中所使用的[[淡水|淡水]]、空气中的[[水蒸气|水蒸气]]，慢慢地形成了云层，云层积累到一定厚度后产生[[雨|雨]]或[[雪|雪]]落到地表，形成[[湖泊|湖泊]]和[[河流|河流]]，最终流向大海。<ref name=NOAAcycle>[[美国国家海洋和大气管理局|NOAA]]. "[http://oceanexplorer.noaa.gov/edu/learning/player/lesson07.html Lesson 7: The Water Cycle] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130425214321/http://oceanexplorer.noaa.gov/edu/learning/player/lesson07.html |date=2013-04-25 }}" in ''Ocean Explorer''. Accessed 19 Apr 2013.</ref>海洋佔據了地球如此大部份，以致於英國作家[[亞瑟·查理斯·克拉克|亞瑟·查理斯·克拉克]]曾記述「地球」（Earth）命名為「海球」（Ocean）會更好。<ref name=Stow />{{rp|page=7}}

研究[[水|水]]以及地球[[水循环|水循環]]的[[科学|科學]]稱為[[水文学|水文學]]；而[[流体力学|流體力學]]則探討水運動時的[[物理学|物理]]現象；最近對於海的研究稱作[[海洋学|海洋學]]。其一開始是研究[[#海流|海流]]的流向<ref>Lee, Sidney (ed.) "[[s:Rennell,_James_(DNB00)|Rennell, James]]" in the ''Dictionary of National Biography'', Vol. 48. Smith, Elder, & Co. (London), 1896. Hosted at [[s:Main_Page|Wikisource]].</ref>，但目前其已涵蓋了广泛且[[科际整合|跨學科]]的主题<ref name="Jenkins">Monkhouse, F.J. (1975) ''Principles of Physical Geography''. pp. 327–328. Hodder & Stoughton. ISBN 978-0-340-04944-0.</ref>，它的研究範疇包括探讨[[#海水|海水]]的特性；研究[[#海浪|海浪]]、[[#潮汐|潮汐]]，以及[[#海流|海流]] ；測绘[[#岸|海岸線]]和[[#海盆|海床]]；並對[[#海洋生物|海洋生物]]進行研究<ref>{{Cite journal | doi = 10.2307/1785367| jstor = 1785367| title = The Seas: Our Knowledge of Life in the Sea and How It is Gained| url = https://archive.org/details/sim_geographical-journal_1929-06_73_6/page/571| journal = The Geographical Journal| volume = 73| issue = 6| page = 571| year = 1929| last1 = b. | first1 = R. N. R.| last2 = Russell | first2 = F. S.|last3 = Yonge | first3 = C. M.}}</ref>。 研究海洋運動以及其力量的分支學科稱為[[物理海洋学|物理海洋学]]<ref>Stewart, Robert H. (2008) [http://oceanworld.tamu.edu/resources/ocng_textbook/PDF_files/book.pdf ''Introduction To Physical Oceanography''] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090327094224/http://oceanworld.tamu.edu/resources/ocng_textbook/PDF_files/book.pdf |date=2009-03-27 }}. pp. 2–3. [[德克萨斯州A&M大学|Texas A & M University]].</ref>。[[海洋生物学|海洋生物学]]則負責研究棲息於[[#棲息地|海洋生態系統]]的生物，包括但不限於[[#動物|動]][[#藻類和植物|植物]]。以上兩者皆受到{{tsl|en|chemical oceanography|化學海洋學}}的研究支持，它研究海洋內的[[化學元素|化學元素]]和[[分子|分子]]的表现：特別是研究[[二氧化碳|二氧化碳]]在[[#海洋酸化|海水酸度增加]]中起了什麼作用，以及海洋在[[#碳循環|碳循環]]中所扮演的角色。海洋[[自然地理學|地理學]]研究海洋的形態和状况，[[海洋地質學|海洋地質學]]則为[[大陆漂移学说|大陆漂移学说]]、[[地球|地球]]的组合方式及其[[地球構造|構造]]提供證據，並使[[沉降|沉降]]的过程弄清，這門學問所獲得的資料可用來協助人們研究[[火山作用|火山作用]]和[[地震学|地震]]<ref name=Jenkins/>。

