海水都带有[[咸味|咸味]]，但不同水域的咸味程度（[[盐度|盐度]]）有所不同，约90%的海水每公升溶解有34-35克的[[固体|固体]]，盐度在3.4-3.5[[%|%]]之间<ref>Pond, Stephen & al. ''Introductory Dynamic Oceanography'', {{nowrap|p. 5}}. Pergamon Press, 1978.</ref>。为了准确描述较小的差异，海洋学家通常用[[千分比|千分比]](‰)或[[千分率|千分率]](ppt)来表示海水的盐度。[[北半球|北半球]]表层海水的盐度约为34‰，而[[南半球|南半球]]表层海水的盐度约为35‰<ref name=reddyornot/>。海水中的[[溶质|溶质]]主要来自[[河流|河流]]和[[海底|海底]]<ref>Pinet, Paul. ''Invitation to Oceanography''. West Publishing Co.（St. Paul, Minnesota）, 1996. ISBN 978-0-314-06339-7.</ref>。但世界海洋的溶质的组分是相似的<ref name=Millero>Millero, Frank & al. "[http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0967063707002282 The Composition of Standard Seawater and the Definition of the Reference-Composition Salinity Scale] {{Wayback|url=http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0967063707002282 |date=20210325011626 }}" in ''Deep Sea Research'', {{nowrap|Part I:}} ''Oceanographic Research Papers'', {{nowrap|Vol. 55}}, {{nowrap|No. 1}}, {{nowrap|pp. 50–72}}. Jan 2008. DOI 10.1016/j.dsr.2007.10.001. Bibcode: 2008DSRI...55...50M.</ref><ref>Swenson, Herbert. "[http://www.palomar.edu/oceanography/salty_ocean.htm Why is the Ocean Salty?] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20010418010043/http://www.palomar.edu/oceanography/salty_ocean.htm |date=2001-04-18 }}" US Geological Survey. Accessed 17 April 2013.</ref>：[[钠离子|钠离子]](Na)和[[氯离子|氯离子]](Cl)占溶质的85%左右。其他溶质包括[[金属离子|金属离子]]如[[镁离子|镁离子]](Mg)，[[钙离子|钙离子]](Ca)，而[[阴离子|阴离子]]包括[[硫酸鹽|硫酸鹽]](SO₄)、[[碳酸根|碳酸根]](CO₃)、[[溴离子|溴离子]]等。由于海水的含盐量过高，所以即使在没有被[[水污染|污染]]的情况下，海水也不能直接饮用{{efn|[[人|Human]] [[腎|kidney]]s excrete [[尿|urine]] that is around 2% saline,<ref name=10hut>[[美国陆军|US Army]] (June 1992). [http://www.basegear.com/ch6.html FM 21–76: ''Survival''] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140808052026/http://www.basegear.com/ch6.html |date=2014-08-08 }}. Chapter 6: "Water Procurement".</ref> so that drinking one liter of most forms of seawater will require drinking at least another liter of freshwater to prevent {{tsl|en|Sodium in biology#Human water and salt balance||harmful}} excesses of sodium. Without this additional water, increased urination to remove the salt produces [[脱水|dehydration]].<ref>NOAA (11 Jan 2013). "[http://oceanservice.noaa.gov/facts/drinksw.html Drinking Seawater Can Be Deadly to Humans] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130921053237/http://oceanservice.noaa.gov/facts/drinksw.html |date=2013-09-21 }}".</ref>}}。同样地，海水也不能在未经淡化的情况下用于灌溉大多数[[植物|植物]]。經一定比例調配的[[人造海水|人造海水]]常用於科学和科技領域。

海水盐度的变化受到众多因素的影响：海洋间的[[洋流|洋流]]、从河流和[[冰川|冰川]]流入的[[淡水|淡水]]、海冰的形成与融化、海水的[[蒸发|蒸发]]、[[降雨|降雨]]，海水的盐度还与[[温度|温度]]，风，[[海浪|海浪]]互相影响。例如，[[波罗的海|波罗的海]]表层海水的盐度很低，约为10－15[[‰|‰]]，这是因为[[北欧|北欧]]较低的气温令海水的[[蒸发量|蒸发量]]较小，且波罗的海有众多的流入河流，由于波罗的海和[[北海_(大西洋)|北海]]连接的海峡较窄，所以波罗的海的表层海水几乎不与寒冷、浓度较大的底层海水混合<ref>Thulin,Jan
& al. "[https://web.archive.org/web/20070606211738/http://www.ices.dk/projects/balticsea/Baltic%20Sea-RSE%20Thulin%20and%20Andrusaitis.pdf Religion, Science, and the Environment Symposium V on the Baltic Sea]". 2003. Hosted at Archive.org, 6 Jun 2007. Accessed 16 Apr 2013.</ref>。与之相反的是位于[[撒哈拉沙漠|撒哈拉沙漠]]、[[阿拉伯沙漠|阿拉伯沙漠]]之间的[[红海|红海]]，海水的盐度平均约为40‰：蒸发量较高，[[沉淀|沉淀]]较少；只有几条且多为[[季节性河流|季节性的流入河流]]；它和其他的海洋相连的通道-北面的[[苏伊士运河|苏伊士运河]]和南面的[[曼德海峡|曼德海峡]]都十分狭窄<ref>{{cite journal |author=Thunell, Robert C.; Locke, Sharon M.; Williams, Douglas F. |year=1988 |title=Glacio-eustatic sea-level control on Red Sea salinity |journal=Nature |volume=334 |pages=601–604 |doi=10.1038/334601a0 |issue=6183 |bibcode = 1988Natur.334..601T }}</ref>。地中海的海水盐度稍低，约为37‰。而[[高鹽湖泊|部分內陸湖則有相當高的鹽度]]，如[[死海|死海]]鹽度達300‰。

