===海洋酸化===
{{Main article|海洋酸化}}
海水是弱碱性的，在工业革命前它的[[pH|pH]]约为8.2。然而最近，人类活动使得大气中[[二氧化碳|二氧化碳]]含量持续增加；大约30-40%增加的CO<sub>2</sub>被海洋吸收，形成[[碳酸|碳酸]]并通过一个被称为海洋酸化的过程降低海水pH<ref name=Feely04>{{Cite journal|doi=10.1126/science.1097329|pmid=15256664|url=http://www.pmel.noaa.gov/pubs/outstand/feel2633/feel2633.shtml|title=Impact of Anthropogenic CO<sub>2</sub> on the CaCO<sub>3</sub> System in the Oceans|journal=Science|volume=305|issue=5682|pages=362–6|year=2004|last1=Feely|first1=R. A.|last2=Sabine|first2=C. L.|last3=Lee|first3=K|last4=Berelson|first4=W|last5=Kleypas|first5=J|last6=Fabry|first6=V. J.|last7=Millero|first7=F. J.|bibcode=2004Sci...305..362F|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131224082802/http://www.pmel.noaa.gov/pubs/outstand/feel2633/feel2633.shtml|archivedate=2013-12-24}}</ref><ref name="Zeebe2008">{{Cite journal | doi = 10.1126/science.1159124|pmid=18599765| title = OCEANS: Carbon Emissions and Acidification| journal = Science| volume = 321| issue = 5885| pages = 51–2| year = 2008| last1 = Zeebe | first1 = R. E.| last2 = Zachos | first2 = J. C.| last3 = Caldeira | first3 = K.| last4 = Tyrrell | first4 = T.}}</ref><ref name="GattusoHansson2011">{{cite book|author1=Gattuso, J.-P.|author2=Hansson, L.|title=Ocean Acidification|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=8yjNFxkALjIC&printsec=frontcover|date=2011|publisher=Oxford University Press|isbn=978-0-19-959109-1|oclc=730413873|access-date=2017-01-03|archive-date=2019-01-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190110093934/https://books.google.com/books?id=8yjNFxkALjIC&printsec=frontcover|dead-url=no}}</ref>（现已低于8.1<ref name="EPA_Ocean_Acidity">{{cite web | title = Ocean Acidity | work = U.S. EPA climate change web site | publisher = [[美国国家环境保护局|EPA]] | date = 2013-09-13 | url = http://www.epa.gov/climatechange/science/indicators/oceans/acidity.html | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20131103114209/http://www.epa.gov/climatechange/science/indicators/oceans/acidity.html | archivedate = 2013-11-03 }}</ref>）。预计到2100年，海水pH可达7.7(这意味着氢离子浓度增加三倍)，这将是长达一个世纪的显著变化。<ref name=AboutAntarctica />{{efn| To help put a change of this magnitude into perspective, when the pH of human blood plasma is raised from its normal 7.4 to a value above 7.8, or lowered to a value below 6.8, death ensues.<ref name="Tanner2012">{{cite book | editor-last = Rhoades | editor-first = R. A. | editor2-last = Bell | editor2-first = D. R. | last = Tanner | first = G. A. | title = Medical Physiology: Principles for Clinical Medicine | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=1kGcFOKCUzkC | contribution = Acid-Base Homeostasis | chapterurl = https://www.inkling.com/read/medical-physiology-rodney-rhoades-david-bell-4th/chapter-24/acidbase-balance-disturbances | date = 2012 | publisher = Lippincott Williams & Wilkins | isbn = 978-1-60913-427-3 | access-date = 2017-01-03 | archive-date = 2021-03-28 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210328101014/https://books.google.com/books?id=1kGcFOKCUzkC | dead-url = no }}</ref>}}

[[钙|钙]]是海洋生物[[骨骼系統|骨骼系統]]的重要组成成分， 但是[[碳酸鈣|碳酸鈣]]在压力的作用下会变得更加容易溶解，因此碳酸盐贝壳和[[骨骼系統|骨骼系統]]会在[[碳酸鹽補償深度|补偿深度]]以下发生溶解。<ref name=Pinet>{{cite book |last=Pinet |first=Paul R. |date=1996 |title=Invitation to Oceanography |pages=126, 134–135 |publisher=West Publishing Company |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=eAqQvGYap24C&printsec=frontcover |isbn=978-0-314-06339-7 |access-date=2017-01-03 |archive-date=2019-01-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190110094617/https://books.google.com/books?id=eAqQvGYap24C&printsec=frontcover |dead-url=no }}</ref> 同时，碳酸钙也会在较低的PH值环境下变得更易溶解，因此海洋酸化可能会对具有石灰质外壳的海洋生物（例如[[牡蛎|牡蛎]]、[[蛤|蛤]]、[[海胆|海胆]]和[[珊瑚|珊瑚]]）有着深远影响，<ref name=PMEL>{{cite web | url=http://www.pmel.noaa.gov/co2/story/What+is+Ocean+Acidification%3F | title=What is Ocean Acidification? | publisher=NOAA PMEL Carbon Program | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130902071022/http://www.pmel.noaa.gov/co2/story/What+is+Ocean+Acidification%3F | archivedate=2013-09-02 | accessdate=2017-01-03 }}</ref>因为他们形成外壳的能力将会减弱，<ref name=orr05>{{Cite journal | last1 = Orr | first1 = J. C. | last2 = Fabry | first2 = V. J. | last3 = Aumont | first3 = O. | last4 = Bopp | first4 = L. | last5 = Doney | first5 = S. C. | last6 = Feely | first6 = R. A. | last7 = Gnanadesikan | first7 = A. | last8 = Gruber | first8 = N. | last9 = Ishida | first9 = A. | doi = 10.1038/nature04095 | last10 = Joos | first10 = F. | last11 = Key | first11 = R. M. | last12 = Lindsay | first12 = K. | last13 = Maier-Reimer | first13 = E. | last14 = Matear | first14 = R. | last15 = Monfray | first15 = P. | last16 = Mouchet | first16 = A. | last17 = Najjar | first17 = R. G. | last18 = Plattner | first18 = G. K. | last19 = Rodgers | first19 = K. B. | last20 = Sabine | first20 = C. L. | last21 = Sarmiento | first21 = J. L. | last22 = Schlitzer | first22 = R. | last23 = Slater | first23 = R. D. | last24 = Totterdell | first24 = I. J. | last25 = Weirig | first25 = M. F. | last26 = Yamanaka | first26 = Y. | last27 = Yool | first27 = A. | title = Anthropogenic ocean acidification over the twenty-first century and its impact on calcifying organisms | journal = Nature | volume = 437 | issue = 7059 | pages = 681–686 | year = 2005 | pmid =  16193043| pmc = |bibcode = 2005Natur.437..681O }}</ref>碳酸盐补偿深度将更接近海面。受影响的[[浮游生物|浮游生物]]将包括被称为[[翼足目|pteropod]]的蜗牛样软体动物, 以及被称为[[鈣板金藻|鈣板金藻]]和[[有孔蟲門|有孔蟲門]]的[[藻類|藻類]]。所有这些都是[[食物鏈|食物鏈]]的重要组成部分，其数量的减少将产生重大后果。在热带地区，[[珊瑚|珊瑚]]可能会受到严重影响，因为它将更难构造其碳酸钙骨架，<ref name="Cohen2009">{{Cite journal | doi = 10.5670/oceanog.2009.102| title = Why Corals Care About Ocean Acidification: Uncovering the Mechanism| journal = Oceanography| volume = 22| issue = 4| pages = 118–127| year = 2009| last1 = Cohen | first1 = A. | last2 = Holcomb | first2 = M. }}</ref> 这将对其他[[珊瑚礁|珊瑚礁]]居民产生不利影响。<ref name=AboutAntarctica>{{cite web |url=http://www.antarctica.gov.au/about-antarctica/environment/climate-change/ocean-acidification-and-the-southern-ocean |title=Ocean acidification |date=2007-09-28 |publisher=Department of Sustainability, Environment, Water, Population & Communities: Australian Antarctic Division |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130426211216/http://www.antarctica.gov.au/about-antarctica/environment/climate-change/ocean-acidification-and-the-southern-ocean |archivedate=2013-04-26 }}</ref>

在地球的地质史中，目前海洋酸化的速度似乎是空前的，这使得我们不清楚海洋生态系统能在多大程度上适应未来的变化。<ref name="Hönisch2012">{{Cite journal | last1 = Honisch | first1 = B. | last2 = Ridgwell | first2 = A. | last3 = Schmidt | first3 = D. N. | last4 = Thomas | first4 = E. | last5 = Gibbs | first5 = S. J. | last6 = Sluijs | first6 = A. | last7 = Zeebe | first7 = R. | last8 = Kump | first8 = L. | last9 = Martindale | first9 = R. C. | last10 = Greene | doi = 10.1126/science.1208277 | first10 = S. E. | last11 = Kiessling | first11 = W. | last12 = Ries | first12 = J. | last13 = Zachos | first13 = J. C. | last14 = Royer | first14 = D. L. | last15 = Barker | first15 = S. | last16 = Marchitto Jr | first16 = T. M. | last17 = Moyer | first17 = R. | last18 = Pelejero | first18 = C. | last19 = Ziveri | first19 = P. | last20 = Foster | first20 = G. L. | last21 = Williams | first21 = B. | title = The Geological Record of Ocean Acidification | journal = Science | volume = 335 | issue = 6072 | pages = 1058–1063 | year = 2012 | pmid =  22383840| pmc = |bibcode = 2012Sci...335.1058H }}</ref>引起特别关注的是，海洋酸化同预期中气候变暖和[[海洋缺氧事件|海洋缺氧事件]]的额外压力的组合会如何影响海洋。<ref name="Gruber2011">{{Cite journal | doi = 10.1098/rsta.2011.0003| title = Warming up, turning sour, losing breath: Ocean biogeochemistry under global change| journal = Philosophical Transactions of the Royal Society A: Mathematical, Physical and Engineering Sciences| volume = 369| issue = 1943| pages = 1980–1996| year = 2011| last1 = Gruber | first1 = N.|bibcode = 2011RSPTA.369.1980G }}</ref>

