=== 藻類和植物 ===
{{main|藻类}}
海洋{{tsl|en|primary producers|初级生产者|初级生产者}}，即浮游生物中的植物以及微生物分布广泛且多种多样。显微[[光合作用|光合]]藻类、浮游植物贡献的光合产量大于世界所有森林所贡献之和。海洋中大约45％的有机物质的[[初级生产|初级生产]]是由[[硅藻|硅藻]]贡献的。<ref>{{Cite journal | doi = 10.1029/2002GB002018| title = Role of diatoms in regulating the ocean's silicon cycle| journal = Global Biogeochemical Cycles| volume = 17| issue = 4| pages = n/a| year = 2003| last1 = Yool | first1 = A. | last2 = Tyrrell | first2 = T. | bibcode=2003GBioC..17.1103Y}}</ref>体型较大的藻类通常被称为[[海藻|海藻]]，它们对于其所在地而言十分重要；[[马尾藻|马尾藻]]形成漂浮物，而[[海带|海带]]形成海底森林。<ref name=DKlife />{{rp|pages=246–255}}海草状的[[被子植物|被子植物]]在水浅的沙地长成“[[草甸|草甸]]”<ref>{{Cite journal | doi = 10.1371/journal.pone.0016504| title = Positive Feedbacks in Seagrass Ecosystems – Evidence from Large-Scale Empirical Data| journal = PLoS ONE| volume = 6| pages = e16504| year = 2011| last1 = Van Der Heide | first1 = T. | last2 = Van Nes | first2 = E. H. | last3 = Van Katwijk | first3 = M. M. | last4 = Olff | first4 = H. | last5 = Smolders | first5 = A. J. P. |bibcode = 2011PLoSO...616504V }}</ref>，[[红树林|红树林]]勾勒热带和亚热带地区的海岸线<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.botgard.ucla.edu/html/botanytextbooks/worldvegetation/marinewetlands/mangal/ |title=Mangal (Mangrove) |publisher=Mildred E. Mathias Botanical Garden |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130921053259/http://www.botgard.ucla.edu/html/botanytextbooks/worldvegetation/marinewetlands/mangal/ |archivedate=2013-09-21 }}</ref>而[[鹽生植物|鹽生植物]]在常被淹没的[[盐碱滩|盐碱滩]]中茁壮生长。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.botgard.ucla.edu/html/botanytextbooks/worldvegetation/marinewetlands/saltmarsh/ |title=Coastal Salt Marsh |publisher=Mildred E. Mathias Botanical Garden |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130921053301/http://www.botgard.ucla.edu/html/botanytextbooks/worldvegetation/marinewetlands/saltmarsh/ |archivedate=2013-09-21 }}</ref>所有这些栖息地能够大量固碳，并支撑体型更大以及更小的动物的[[生物多样性|生物多样性]]。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.unesco.org/new/en/natural-sciences/ioc-oceans/priority-areas/rio-20-ocean/blueprint-for-the-future-we-want/marine-biodiversity/facts-and-figures-on-marine-biodiversity/ |title=Facts and figures on marine biodiversity |date=2012 |work=Marine biodiversity |publisher=UNESCO |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130703103639/http://www.unesco.org/new/en/natural-sciences/ioc-oceans/priority-areas/rio-20-ocean/blueprint-for-the-future-we-want/marine-biodiversity/facts-and-figures-on-marine-biodiversity/ |archivedate=2013-07-03 }}</ref>

阳光只能穿透海水顶部{{convert|200|m|sp=us|abbr=on}}的区域，所以植物只能在海洋的这一部分生长。<ref name=Russell />海洋表层通常缺乏具有生物活性的含氮化合物。海洋[[氮循环|氮循环]]由复杂的微生物转化组成，包括[[固氮作用|固氮作用]]、[[同化_(生物学)|同化]]、[[硝化作用|硝化作用]]、[[厌氧氨氧化菌|厌氧氨氧化]]和[[反硝化反应|反硝化反应]]。<ref>{{Cite journal | doi = 10.1098/rstb.2013.0121| title = The marine nitrogen cycle: Recent discoveries, uncertainties and the potential relevance of climate change| journal = Philosophical Transactions of the Royal Society B: Biological Sciences| volume = 368| issue = 1621| page = 20130121| year = 2013| last1 = Voss | first1 = M.| last2 = Bange | first2 = H. W.| last3 = Dippner | first3 = J. W.| last4 = Middelburg | first4 = J. J.| last5 = Montoya | first5 = J. P.| last6 = Ward | first6 = B.}}</ref>这些过程中有一些在深水中发生，因而在冷水[[上升流|上升流]]或者能够获得从陆地来的营养物质的靠近河口三角洲的海域植物生长的更高。这意味着，最富有生产力即富含浮游生物既而也富含鱼类的地区主要是沿海地区。<ref name=Stow />{{rp|pages=160–163}}

