=== 貿易 ===
{{Main article|航运|贸易}}

[[File:Shipping_routes_red_black.png|thumb]]

当[[苏美尔|苏美尔文明]]与[[印度河流域文明|印度河流域文明]]相连，早期人类[[文明|文明]]就已开始从事水上贸易<ref>Gosch, Stephen S. (2007) ''Premodern Travel in World History''. Taylor & Francis. ISBN 0-203-92695-1.</ref>。大约公元前2000世纪，[[克里特|克里特岛]]上的[[米诺斯文明|米诺斯人]]确立了最早的[[制海权|制海权]]，一个极大程度上依靠的贸易和海军实力的沿海帝国<ref>Hägg, R. (1994) ''The Minoan Thalassocracy: Myth and Reality''. (Stockholm).</ref>。[[腓尼基|腓尼基]][[城邦|城邦]]和[[古希腊|古希腊]]城邦在公元前1200世纪取代了米诺斯人，最终建立了从[[亚速海|亚速海]]至[[索维拉|索维拉]]的[[古代殖民地|广阔古代殖民地]]<ref>Greer, Thomas (2004). [https://books.google.com/books?id=DR4MKjXY_MMC&pg=PA63 A Brief History of the Western World] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=DR4MKjXY_MMC&pg=PA63 |date=20200525113233 }}. p. 63. Thomson Wadsworth. ISBN 978-0-534-64236-5.</ref>。在罗马帝国时期，商贸也一如既往地繁荣。在公元前一世纪，游牧民族的入侵中断了印度获得西伯利亚黄金，使得印度开启了前往[[马来西亚|马来西亚]]和印度尼西亚的海上航线<ref>Shaffer, Lynda (2001). "Southernization" in ''Agricultural and Pastoral Societies in Ancient and Classical History''. Temple University Press. ISBN 1-56639-832-0.</ref>，也使得首次接触到[[印度教|印度教]]和[[穆斯林|穆斯林]]商人。随着罗马帝国的衰落，欧洲大陆的贸易规模缩小，但仍在世界的其他角落繁荣兴旺<ref>{{cite book |title=Cross-Cultural Trade in World History |last=Curtin |first=Philip D. |date=1984 |publisher=Cambridge University Press |isbn=978-0-521-26931-5 |pages=88–104 |url=https://books.google.com/?id=R4IiYFhliv4C&printsec=frontcover}}</ref>。当时的[[泰米尔人|泰米尔]][[朱罗王朝|朱罗王朝]]凭借贸易与[[唐朝|唐朝]]、爪哇[[三佛齐|三佛齐]]，西面的[[阿拔斯王朝|阿拔斯王朝]]繁地来往。随着阿拉伯人不断地[[穆斯林的征服|东征西讨]]，他们逐渐占领了[[印度洋|印度洋]]的海上贸易，也将[[伊斯兰教|伊斯兰教]]沿着东非洲沿岸，最终传播至东南亚<ref>{{cite book | title=A Comparison of Medieval Arab Methods of Navigation with Those of the Pacific Islands | publisher=Coimbra | author=Tibbets, Gerald Randall | date=1979}}</ref>。[[地理大发现|地理大发现]]主要的影响是将世界的区域贸易网络统一为单一的世界性市场，主要由欧洲各君主、[[阿姆斯特丹|阿姆斯特丹]]和[[伦敦|伦敦]]的商人及其他大西洋港口推动而成。从16世纪到19世纪，大约1.3亿人口通过船运，被卖到大西洋对岸的美洲当奴隶<ref>{{cite book |title=The Atlantic Slave Trade: Effects on Africa |last=Kubetzek |first=Kathrin |last2=Kant |first2=Karo |date=2012 |publisher=GRIN Verlag |isbn=978-3-656-15818-9 |page=1 |url=https://books.google.com/?id=jSg1G5gKNsIC}}</ref>。黑尔斯奖的设立就是为了奖励最短时间内穿越大西洋的商业航线，1952年，{{link-en|美国号邮轮|SS United States}}获得了当时3天10小时40分钟的最快记录<ref>{{cite journal |author=Smith, Jack |date=1985 |title=Hales Trophy, won in 1952 by ''SS United States'' remains at King's Point as ''Challenger'' succumbs to the sea |journal=Yachting |issue=November |page=121 |url=https://books.google.com/?id=BLg5v41rbmEC&pg=PA121}}</ref>。

如今，大批的商品通过海路运输，尤其是横跨大西洋地区和环太平洋地区。主要的贸易航线是从[[海格力斯之柱|直布罗陀海峡]]以及[[马六甲海峡|马六甲海峡]]跨越地中海和[[苏伊士运河|苏伊士运河]]到达印度海，还有许多贸易航线也会通过[[英吉利海峡|英吉利海峡]]<ref>{{Cite journal| doi = 10.1126/science.1149345| url = http://micheli.stanford.edu/pdf/30-Halpernetal2008Science.pdf| bibcode = 2008Sci...319..948H| pmid = 18276889| title = A Global Map of Human Impact on Marine Ecosystems| journal = Science| volume = 319| issue = 5865| pages = 948–52| year = 2008| last1 = Halpern| first1 = B. S.| last2 = Walbridge| first2 = S.| last3 = Selkoe| first3 = K. A.| last4 = Kappel| first4 = C. V.| last5 = Micheli| first5 = F.| last6 = d'Agrosa| first6 = C.| last7 = Bruno| first7 = J. F.| last8 = Casey| first8 = K. S.| last9 = Ebert| first9 = C.| last10 = Fox| first10 = H. E.| last11 = Fujita| first11 = R.| last12 = Heinemann| first12 = D.| last13 = Lenihan| first13 = H. S.| last14 = Madin| first14 = E. M. P.| last15 = Perry| first15 = M. T.| last16 = Selig| first16 = E. R.| last17 = Spalding| first17 = M.| last18 = Steneck| first18 = R.| last19 = Watson| first19 = R.| deadurl = no| archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20130504112138/http://micheli.stanford.edu/pdf/30-Halpernetal2008Science.pdf| archivedate = 2013-05-04}}</ref>。[[Shipping_lane|船运航线]]指的是货轮在公海上的航线，习惯上是利用信风和气流运输。世界上百分之60以上的集装箱运输是由最主要20条航线完成的<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.worldshipping.org/about-the-industry/global-trade/trade-routes |title=Trade routes |publisher=World Shipping Council |access-date=2017-01-03 |archive-date=2014-10-22 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6TVxR8V1s?url=http://www.worldshipping.org/about-the-industry/global-trade/trade-routes |dead-url=no }}</ref>。 从2007年开始，北极冰川不断融化，使得去往[[西北水道|西北航道]]的船只在夏季的一段时间里，可以绕开苏伊士运河或[[巴拿马运河|巴拿马运河]]的较长路线<ref>{{cite web | url=http://news.nationalgeographic.co.uk/news/2007/09/070917-northwest-passage.html | title=Arctic Melt Opens Northwest Passage | publisher=National Geographic | date=2007-09-17 | author=Roach, John | deadurl=no | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140222182835/http://news.nationalgeographic.co.uk/news/2007/09/070917-northwest-passage.html | archivedate=2014-02-22 }}</ref>。运输方式通过[[air_freight|空运]]补充，这是一个更昂贵的运输方法，大多数用于极其贵重货物和易腐货物。海上贸易每年至少承载了4亿美元价值的货物<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.worldshipping.org/about-the-industry/global-trade |title=Global trade |publisher=World Shipping Council |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6TVxSNk7r?url=http://www.worldshipping.org/about-the-industry/global-trade |archivedate=2014-10-22 |accessdate=2017-01-03 }}</ref>。

海运贸易的货物通常分为两种：[[商品|大宗货物]]和[[日用品|杂货]]（又称[[货物|普通货物]]），这种大部分现在已经通过[[集装箱|集装箱]]运输。商品是液体、粉末或碎木料通常零散地放在[[散货船|散货船]]的[[货舱|货舱]]中，连同油、谷物、煤炭、矿石、废金属和沙石一起。杂货通常是产成品，并且以包裹的形式运输，堆在[[栈板|栈板]]上。在1950年集装箱发明之前，这些货物都是零碎地装载、运输、卸货<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dtic.mil/cgi-bin/GetTRDoc?AD=ADA439918&Location=U2&doc=GetTRDoc.pdf |author=Joint Chief of Staff |authorlink= |title=Bulk cargo |date=2005-08-31 |work=Department of Defense Dictionary of Military and Associated Terms |publisher=Department of Defense |location=Washington DC |page=73 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110604203854/http://www.dtic.mil/cgi-bin/GetTRDoc?AD=ADA439918&Location=U2&doc=GetTRDoc.pdf |archivedate=2011-06-04 }}</ref>。 使用集装箱极大程度低高了运输效率也减少了移动成本<ref>{{cite journal |date=1958-05-22 |department=News and Comments |journal=New Scientist |volume=4 |issue=79 |page=10 |title=Fork lift trucks aboard |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=nJa21Dy8XxwC&lpg=PA10 |author=Reed Business Information |access-date=2017-01-03 |archive-date=2020-05-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200525113323/https://books.google.com/books?id=nJa21Dy8XxwC&lpg=PA10 |dead-url=no }}</ref>，如今，大多数货物以统一大小，封闭地集装箱运输，并装载在配有特定用途的[[货柜船|货柜船]]上。<ref name=Sauerbier>{{cite book |author=Sauerbier, Charles L. |author2=Meurn, Robert J. |title=Marine Cargo Operations: a guide to stowage |publisher=Cornell Maritime Press |location=Cambridge, Md |date=2004 |pages=1–16 |isbn=0-87033-550-2 }}</ref> [[货运代理|货运代理]]公司负责登记货物，安排提取和运输，以及管理证明文件。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://dictionary.infoplease.com/freight-forwarder#ixzz2FhueT97J |title=Freight forwarder |date=1997 |work=Random House Unabridged Dictionary |publisher=Random House |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130117114301/http://dictionary.infoplease.com/freight-forwarder#ixzz2FhueT97J |archivedate=2013-01-17 |accessdate=2017-01-03 }}</ref> 运输安全由[[国际海事组织|国际海事组织]]管理，1959年在伦敦总部首次发起召集。监管对象包括了发展与维系运输、海上安全、环境问题、法律事务、技术协作和海事保全的监管框架<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.imo.org/About/Pages/Default.aspx | title=Introduction to IMO | publisher=International Maritime Organization | date=2013 | access-date=2017-01-03 | archive-date=2014-10-22 | archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6TVxU8w1E?url=http://www.imo.org/About/Pages/Default.aspx | dead-url=no }}</ref>。

