海洋牧場於2010年共生產了7,900萬[[公噸|公噸]]（8,700萬[[短吨|短吨]]）的食物及非食物產品，其中中包括野生物種，約養殖了600種植物及動物，部分用於培育野生物種。養殖的動物包括[[鱼|鱼]]、水生[[爬行动物|爬行动物]]、甲殼類動物、軟體動物、[[海參|海參]]、[[海膽|海膽]]、海鞘及水母。<ref>{{cite book |url=http://www.fao.org/docrep/016/i2727e/i2727e00.htm |title=The State of World Fisheries and Aquaculture 2012 |date=2012 |isbn=978-92-5-107225-7 |publisher=FAO Fisheries and Aquaculture Department |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161111221805/http://www.fao.org/docrep/016/i2727e/i2727e00.htm |archivedate=2016-11-11 }}</ref>。綜合{{tsl|en|mariculture|海水養殖}}的好處包括有穩定的浮游生物來源，而且動物的廢棄物會自然清除<ref>{{cite book |url=http://www.fao.org/docrep/012/i1092e/i1092e00.htm |title=Integrated mariculture |editor=Soto, D. |date=2009 |work=Fisheries and Aquaculture Technical Paper. No. 529 |publisher=FAO |isbn=978-92-5-106387-3 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130604150735/http://www.fao.org/docrep/012/i1092e/i1092e00.htm |archivedate=2013-06-04 }}</ref>，若是一些廢棄物可能會造成損害的情形，可以使用{{tsl|en|integrated multi-trophic aquaculture|綜合多物種海水養殖}}，例如養殖鮭魚時同時養殖[[貝類|貝類]]，鮭魚的排泄物即為貝類的食物來源。海水養殖有許多不同的方式，有鳍鱼类的網罩可以悬挂在外海，网箱則較常用在較受保護的水域，也可以放在漲潮時海水會流進的池塘中，[[海蝦養殖|海蝦養殖]]會在有連接外海的浅水池中養殖<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.shrimpnews.com/About.html |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100201223644/http://www.shrimpnews.com/About.html |archivedate=2010-02-01 |title=About shrimp farming |publisher=Shrimp News International}}</ref>。掛在水中的繩索可以生長藻類，牡蠣和貽貝。牡蠣則是在托盤上或是網狀管上飼養。海參是在海底養殖<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.worldfishcenter.org/featured/sea-cucumber-ranching-improves-livelihoods |title=Sea cucumber ranching improves livelihoods |publisher=WorldFish |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130523062648/http://www.worldfishcenter.org/featured/sea-cucumber-ranching-improves-livelihoods |archivedate=2013-05-23 }}</ref>。[[緬因州|緬因州]]有[[海螯蝦|海螯蝦]]的圈養育種計劃，作法是將[[幼体|幼体]]放置在海中，因此使海螯蝦的收獲量增加<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.marinebio.net/marinescience/06future/lobsterfarm.htm |title=Lobster mariculture |author=Anderson, Genny |date=2009-06-15 |work=Marine Science |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121030040906/http://www.marinebio.net/marinescience/06future/lobsterfarm.htm |archivedate=2012-10-30 }}</ref>。人類食用的藻類超過145種，包括紅藻、綠藻、褐藻等，在日本及其他亞洲國家有悠久的養殖歷史，{{tsl|en|algaculture|藻類養殖}}仍具有相當潛力。<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/magazine-18813075 | title=Future foods: What will we be eating in 20 years' time? | publisher=BBC | date=2012-07-30 | author=Winterman, Denise | deadurl=no | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130517071823/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/magazine-18813075 | archivedate=2013-05-17 }}</ref>少數海洋開花植物供食用，如[[海蓬子|海蓬子]]，能夠生食或經烹飪。<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.bbcgoodfood.com/content/knowhow/glossary/samphire/ | title=Samphire | publisher=BBC: Good Food | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070527114751/http://www.bbcgoodfood.com/content/knowhow/glossary/samphire/ | archivedate=2007-05-27 | access-date=2017-01-03 }}</ref>因水產養殖多為養殖單一物種，面臨廣泛傳染{{tsl|en|Fish diseases and parasites|魚類疾病及寄生生物|疾病}}的風險。如1990年代中國養殖[[栉孔扇贝|栉孔扇贝]]、[[明蝦|明蝦]]受大規模疾病影響，而必須更換養殖物種。<ref>"[http://china.nlambassade.org/binaries/content/assets/postenweb/c/china/zaken-doen-in-china/import/kansen_en_sectoren/agrofood/rapporten_over_agro_food/an-overview-of-chinas-aquaculture An Overview of China's Aquaculture] {{webarchive|url=http://archive.wikiwix.com/cache/20140814170115/http://china.nlambassade.org/binaries/content/assets/postenweb/c/china/zaken-doen-in-china/import/kansen_en_sectoren/agrofood/rapporten_over_agro_food/an-overview-of-chinas-aquaculture |date=2014-08-14 }}", p. 6. Netherlands Business Support Office (Dalian), 2010.</ref> [[海蝦養殖|海蝦養殖]]也造成[[东南亚|东南亚]]地區重要的[[红树林|红树林]]遭破壞。<ref>{{Cite book |editor=Steele, John H. |editor2=Thorpe, Steve A. |editor3=Turekian, Karl K.|publisher=Academic Press | doi = 10.1006/rwos.2001.0487| chapter = Mariculture, Environmental, Economic and Social Impacts of| title = Encyclopedia of Ocean Sciences|url=https://archive.org/details/encyclopediaocea00stee | pages = [https://archive.org/details/encyclopediaocea00stee/page/n1709 1578]–1584| year = 2001| last1 = Black | first1 = K. D. | isbn = 9780122274305}}</ref>

