=== 旅行 ===
{{further information|航运}}
以小型私人船只为个人交通工具无疑可以追溯到史前阶段，但能够勇敢开拓海洋的大型船舶在大多数人类历史上通常专门用于贸易或捕鱼。即使是军事运动也常常只是雇佣或指挥这些私人船队作为部队运输，交易员，朝圣者和富有的古代和中世纪的游客。探险和殖民化航程的资金通常由王权从海军基金提供;而运输则不同，他们通常得到特许或者进行购买，然后在初始结算后用于运输供应。在16和17世纪，有专用且定期的本地客运服务，但1817的（Black Ball）黑球是第一个跨大西洋客运线。在[[航海時代|航海时代]]，这种航程的持续时间很大程度上取决于[[盛行风|盛行风]]和天气。18世纪的马盖特侯爵在英国和爱尔兰开始休闲旅游的普及<ref>Lickorish, Leonard (1997). [https://books.google.com/books?id=9HBZh2Lkm04C&pg=PA16 ''Introduction to Tourism''] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=9HBZh2Lkm04C&pg=PA16 |date=20210325014935 }}. p. 16. Butterworth–Heinemann (Oxford). ISBN 1136391916</ref>，后来他在下个世纪与托马斯·库克的旅行团合作。<ref>Hazbun, Waleed (2007). [https://books.google.com/books?id=kCNiWjUjJokC&pg=PA5 "The East as an Exhibit: Thomas Cook & Son and the Origins of the International Tourism Industry in Egypt"] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=kCNiWjUjJokC&pg=PA5 |date=20210325013235 }}, p. 5 in ''The Business of Tourism: Place, Faith, and History''. University of Pennsylvania Press. ISBN 0812239687</ref>在19世纪，蒸汽驱动的远洋客轮连接了世界的铁路网络。到1900年，横渡大西洋大约需要五天，客运线竞争赢得[[藍絲帶獎_(船舶)|蓝丝带奖]]，这是一个非正式的荣誉，给予最快的班轮定期服务。从1909年的二十年，平均速度26.06节（48.26公里/小时）的毛里塔尼亚号赢得此奖。<ref>Newman, Jeff. "[http://www.greatships.net/riband.html The Blue Riband of the North Atlantic] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090310161237/http://www.greatships.net/riband.html |date=2009-03-10 }}". ''Great Ships''.</ref> 这个时代更快更便宜的洲际航班得以实现，最重要的是1958年纽约——巴黎航线<ref>Norris, Gregory (1981). [https://books.google.com/?id=IDEDAAAAMBAJ&lpg=PA28 "Evolution of Cruising"], p. 28 in ''Cruise Travel''.</ref>

海上仍然是娱乐划船和大型游轮的场所。它也是难民和经济移民的一条路线，一些人使用经不住海上风浪的小艇，一些人选择偷渡。 这些人中有的是为了逃离迫害，而许多人是为了到达他们心中前景更加光明的国家，也就是经济移民。<ref>{{cite news |title=No evidence to support Foreign Minister Bob Carr's economic migrants claims |url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/2013-08-14/no-evidence-bob-carr-economic-migrants/4821544 |newspaper=ABC News |date=2013-08-15 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130917022719/http://www.abc.net.au/news/2013-08-14/no-evidence-bob-carr-economic-migrants/4821544 |archivedate=2013-09-17 }}</ref>

=== 休閒活動 ===
{{Main article|巡航|航海|娛樂漁船海釣}}
自19世紀起，人們開始懂得利用海域進行休閒娛樂活動，而在二十世紀更是蓬勃發展。<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.icomia.com/ | title=The voice of the recreational marine industry worldwide | publisher=International Council of Marine Industry Associations | date=2013 | deadurl=no | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130523085458/http://www.icomia.com/ | archivedate=2013-05-23 }}</ref> 海域休閒娛樂活動的種類十分廣泛，包含自由航行、遊艇駕駛、離岸動力船舶競賽<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.yachtingmagazine.com/ |title=Yachting |publisher=YachtingMagazine.com |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080509100343/http://www.yachtingmagazine.com/ |archivedate=2008-05-09 |accessdate=2017-01-03 }}</ref>和休閒娛樂海釣；<ref>{{cite book | title=Global Challenges in Recreational Fisheries | url=https://archive.org/details/globalchallenges00aaso | publisher=John Wiley and Sons | date=2008 |isbn=0-470-69814-4| editor=Aas, Øystein |page=[https://archive.org/details/globalchallenges00aaso/page/n16 5]}}</ref>也包含商業規劃的郵輪巡航；<ref>{{cite book | title=Cruise Ship Tourism | url=https://archive.org/details/cruiseshiptouris00dowl_722 | publisher=CABI|isbn=1-84593-049-5 | date=2006 | editor=Dowling, Ross Kingston |page=[https://archive.org/details/cruiseshiptouris00dowl_722/page/n24 3]}}</ref>以及一些類似透過小型船舶載運的生態旅遊，例如賞鯨和賞海鳥活動等。<ref>{{cite book | title=Marine Ecotourism: Between the Devil and the Deep Blue Sea | url=https://archive.org/details/marineecotourism00cate | publisher=CABI | last1=Cater | first1=Carl |last2=Cater |first2=Erlet | date=2007 |page=[https://archive.org/details/marineecotourism00cate/page/n17 8] |isbn=1-84593-260-9}}</ref>

[[File:Diver_is_cleaning_aquarium_in_California_Academy_of_Sciences_1.jpg|thumb]]
人們喜愛於海中探險：当其他人在[[游泳|游泳]]或在沙滩上休息时，孩子们可以在浅海中划水泼水。18世纪的欧洲，{{tsl|en|William Buchan (physician)|威廉·巴肯}}提倡通过{{tsl|en|sea bathing|海浴}}这种锻炼方式保持身体健康。在海浴成为一种时尚之后，孩子们划水的场景就不特别常见了。<!--This was not always the case, with  becoming the vogue in Europe in the 18th century after  advocated the practice for health reasons. --><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.medclick.co.uk/content/article/157/Health-Benefits-of-Sea-Bathing |title=Health Benefits of Sea Bathing |publisher=MedClick |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130719153347/http://www.medclick.co.uk/content/article/157/Health-Benefits-of-Sea-Bathing |archivedate=2013-07-19 }}</ref> [[衝浪|衝浪]]是一种冲浪者驾驭在浪上（无论是否使用{{tsl|en|surfing board|冲浪板}}）的运动。其它的{{tsl|en|Surface water sports|水面运动}}还包括[[風箏衝浪|風箏衝浪]]：一种{{tsl|en|power kite|动力风筝}}驱动水面上载人板的运动；<ref>{{Cite journal | doi = 10.1177/0363546503262162|pmid=15150038| title = A Prospective Study of Kitesurfing Injuries| url = https://archive.org/details/sim_american-journal-of-sports-medicine_2004-06_32_4/page/921| journal = American Journal of Sports Medicine| volume = 32| issue = 4| pages = 921–927 | year = 2004| last1 = Nickel | first1 = C.|last2=Zernial |first2=O. |last3=Musahl |first3=V. |last4=Hansen|first4=U. |last5=Zantop|first5=T. |last6=Petersen |first6=W. }}</ref>滑浪風帆則是透過固定動力的可操作性的航行活動；<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.worldofwindsurfing.net/en/press-lounge/basic-knowledge/disciplines.html |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130925032923/http://www.worldofwindsurfing.net/en/press-lounge/basic-knowledge/disciplines.html |archivedate=2013-09-25 |title=The disciplines of windsurfing |date=2013-04-15 |publisher=World of Windsurfing }}</ref> 滑水則是透過動力船舶的拖拉來進行滑水。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.abc-of-skiing.com/water-skiing/disciplines.asp |title=Water skiing disciplines |publisher=ABC of Skiing |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130602040620/http://www.abc-of-skiing.com/water-skiing/disciplines.asp |archivedate=2013-06-02 }}</ref>

在水面以下的地方，[[自由潛水|自由潛水]]必要地被限制在浅水区域。{{tsl|en|Pearl hunting|珍珠猎手}}则会按照传统的方式，将油涂抹在他们的皮肤上，将棉花放在耳朵中，用夹子夹上鼻子，带着篮子下潜到{{convert|40|ft|sp=us|abbr=on}}的深度来收集[[珍珠贝|珍珠贝]]。<ref>{{cite book | last = Catelle | first = W. R. | title = The Pearl: Its Story, Its Charm, and Its Value | url = http://www.farlang.com/gemstones/catelle-the-pearl/page_171 | date = 1907 | publisher = J. B. Lippincott | chapter = Methods of Fishing | page = 171 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20130921060017/http://www.farlang.com/gemstones/catelle-the-pearl/page_171 | archivedate = 2013-09-21 }}</ref>人眼不适应在水下工作，但通过[[潛水面鏡|潛水面鏡]]，人能够提高在水下的视力。其它游泳的装备也包括[[蛙鞋|蛙鞋]]和[[浮潜|浮潜]]。 {{tsl|en|Scuba set|水肺潛水設備}}则使水下呼吸变得可能，使人能够在水下活动数小时。<ref name=usn>{{cite book |title=US Navy Diving Manual, 6th revision |date=2006 |publisher=US Naval Sea Systems Command |url=http://www.supsalv.org/00c3_publications.asp?destPage=00c3&pageID=3.9 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080502023541/http://www.supsalv.org/00c3_publications.asp?destPage=00c3&pageId=3.9 |archivedate=2008-05-02 }}</ref>潜水者所能达到的深度与能待在水下的时间，被潜水者所受的压力的增长和回到水面后发生的[[減壓症|減壓症]]的预防需要的限制。<!--  The depths that can be reached by divers and the length of time they can stay underwater is limited by the increase of pressure they experience as they descend and the need to prevent [[減壓症|減壓症]] as they return to the surface. -->休闲潜水者被建议在{{convert|100|ft|sp=us}}的深度以下进行浅水，[[氮醉|氮醉]]的风险会随着下潜深度的上升而上升。<!-- Recreational divers are advised to restrict themselves to depths of under  beyond which the danger of increases.-->通过特殊的装备与训练，{{tsl|en|Deep diving|深海潛水}}也变得可能。<ref name=usn />

=== 發電 ===
{{Main article|海洋能|離岸風力發電}}
[[File:Barrage_de_la_Rance.jpg|thumb]]：約一公里長度的 [[潮汐發電站|潮汐發電站]]，每年可產生540千瓦·時的電力，大約可供[[布列塔尼半岛|布列塔尼半岛]]總用電量的3%（2011）。<ref>{{cite web | title=Offshore Wind Energy in France | url=http://www.th-nuernberg.de/fileadmin/Fachbereiche/bw/studienschwerpunkte/international_business/Master/CAIFD/SeminarPapers/Wind_Offshore_France_Seminar_Paper.pdf | author=Ovdak, Alla | date=2013 | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140808045824/http://www.th-nuernberg.de/fileadmin/Fachbereiche/bw/studienschwerpunkte/international_business/Master/CAIFD/SeminarPapers/Wind_Offshore_France_Seminar_Paper.pdf | archivedate=2014-08-08 }}</ref>]]

海洋蘊藏大量且不同種類的能量，例如：海浪、潮汐變化、鹽度差異、海水溫差等，都能經過有效設計與利用進而來發電。<ref name=OES>{{cite web | url=http://www.ocean-energy-systems.org/ocean_energy/ | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120505152449/http://www.ocean-energy-systems.org/ocean_energy/ | archivedate=2012-05-05 | title=Ocean Energy | publisher=Ocean Energy Systems | date=2011 }}</ref> 這類[[可再生能源|再生能源]]或[[清潔能源|綠能]]包含：[[潮汐能|潮汐能]]、[[海流能|海流能]]、[[海水鹽差能|海水鹽差能]]、[[海水溫差發電|海水溫差（能）]]與[[波浪能|波浪能]]等等。<ref name=OES /><ref>{{cite book | title=Ocean Wave Energy – Current Status and Future Perspectives | url=https://archive.org/details/oceanwaveenergyc00cruz | last1=Cruz |first1=João | publisher=Springer | date=2008 |page=[https://archive.org/details/oceanwaveenergyc00cruz/page/n2 2] | isbn=3-540-74894-6}}</ref>

潮汐能電廠是利用漲退潮的潮差來發電，有時也會利用築水壩（又稱[[潮汐堰壩|潮汐堰壩]]）儲存水，而發電時製造勢能差來發電。全世界第一個啟用的潮汐能電廠：為1967年啟用的法國蘭斯攔水壩，長度約1公里長（約0.62英哩），位於布列塔尼半岛的圣马洛附近，其上的潮汐能發電廠每年可產生0.5兆瓦的電能，但後續也有類似蘭斯攔河壩的計劃。<ref name=Stow />{{rp|pages=111–112}}

能夠提供高度且有效的波浪能，同時也存在著（機組）被波浪能撞擊與破壞的問題，製造能夠負擔且可靠度高的波浪發電機組待開發與改進。目前世界上有一個可產生2兆瓦電能的商業波浪能電廠，名為魚鷹（Osprey）電廠，1995年進造於北蘇格蘭，離岸約300公尺（約1000英呎）。然而，目前此波浪能電廠將因長期波浪拍打、風暴而已近於毀損狀態。<ref name=Stow />{{rp|page=112}}[[海流能|海流能]]可以有效提供近海人口稠密區域的部分電能需求<ref name="doi">{{cite web | title=Ocean Current Energy Potential on the U.S. Outer Continental Shelf | url=http://ocsenergy.anl.gov/documents/docs/OCS_EIS_WhitePaper_Current.pdf | author=US Department of the Interior | date=May 2006 | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110516193629/http://ocsenergy.anl.gov/documents/docs/OCS_EIS_WhitePaper_Current.pdf | archivedate=2011-05-16 | access-date=2017-01-03 }}</ref>。原則上, 利用[[潮汐流發電機|潮汐流發電機]]，海床將也可被使用，但海床的使用將受限於機組，通常海洋深度約40公尺（130英呎）以內可建立。<ref>{{Cite journal | doi = 10.1016/j.renene.2007.04.008| title = Marine-current power generation by diffuser-augmented floating hydro-turbines| journal = Renewable Energy| volume = 33| issue = 4| pages = 665–673| year = 2008| last1 = Ponta | first1 = F. L. | last2 = Jacovkis | first2 = P. M. }}</ref>

離岸風力發電是將風力發動機建在海上，好處為通常海上的風力會高於陸上的風力，因此建立[[風力發電廠|風力發電廠]]通常會選址於離岸的區域。<ref name=Lynn>{{cite book |author=Lynn, Paul A. |title=Onshore and Offshore Wind Energy: An Introduction |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=LymN9n4ukMcC |year=2011 |publisher=John Wiley & Sons |isbn=978-1-119-96142-0 |access-date=2017-01-03 |archive-date=2021-03-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210325013416/https://books.google.com/books?id=LymN9n4ukMcC |dead-url=no }}</ref> 全世界第一個離岸風力發電廠於1991年建立於丹麥，<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.eesi.org/files/offshore_wind_101310.pdf |title=Offshore Wind Energy |author=Environmental and Energy Study Institute |date=October 2010 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110717133335/http://www.eesi.org/files/offshore_wind_101310.pdf |archivedate=2011-07-17 }}</ref>且歐洲的離岸風力電廠裝置容量，預計2010年可達生產3兆瓦電能的目標。<ref name=Tillessen>{{cite magazine |title=High demand for wind farm installation vessels | author=Tillessen, Teena | magazine=Hansa International Maritime Journal | pages=170–171 | date=2010 | volume=147 | issue=8}}</ref>

另外，發電廠通常會建立於於海岸邊或河口旁，如此便可將海洋或河川等水體，當成其發電機組之散熱設施。若協助發電機組散熱之水體溫度越低，則能夠使機組更有發電的效率，尤其對於核電廠而言，良好散熱能力為最重要因素之一。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.world-nuclear.org/info/Current-and-Future-Generation/Cooling-Power-Plants/ |title=Cooling power plants |date=2013-09-01 |publisher=World Nuclear Association |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130921053528/http://www.world-nuclear.org/info/Current-and-Future-Generation/Cooling-Power-Plants/ |archivedate=2013-09-21 }}</ref>

=== 採掘業 ===
{{Main article|離岸鑽井|深海採礦}}
[[File:Reverse_osmosis_desalination_plant.JPG|thumb]]来进行[[海水淡化|海水淡化]]的工厂]]

在海床下的岩石大量的[[石油|petroleum]] (as oil and [[天然气|natural gas]])。原油或燃氣由[[石油平台|石油平台]]及[[钻机|钻机]]{{tsl|en|Offshore drilling|海上鑽井|抽取}}及儲存，稍後被運輸到陸地。基於遙距及嚴酷的環境，離岸石油及燃氣開採具有困難性<ref>{{cite web |url=http://science.howstuffworks.com/environmental/energy/offshore-drilling.htm |title=How offshore drilling works |author=Lamb, Robert |date=2011 |work=HowStuffWorks |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130521042914/http://science.howstuffworks.com/environmental/energy/offshore-drilling.htm |archivedate=2013-05-21 }}</ref>。在海洋抽取原油對環境會做成衝擊。勘探藏量時產生的[[地震波|地震波]]可令動物迷失方向，很可能是[[鯨魚擱淺|鯨魚擱淺]]的原因<ref>{{cite web|last1=Nixon|first1=Robin|title=Oil Drilling: Risks and Rewards|url=http://www.livescience.com/4979-oil-drilling-risks-rewards.html|website=LiveScience|date=2008-06-25|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141217002057/http://www.livescience.com/4979-oil-drilling-risks-rewards.html|archivedate=2014-12-17}}</ref>。[[汞|汞]]、[[鉛|鉛]]和[[砷|砷]]等有毒物質可能被釋放到海洋。開採設施也可能会因为受损而原油洩漏<ref>{{cite web |url=http://science.howstuffworks.com/environmental/energy/offshore-drilling-controversy2.htm |title=Effects of offshore drilling: energy vs. environment |author=Horton, Jennifer |date=2011 |work=HowStuffWorks |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130429153411/http://science.howstuffworks.com/environmental/energy/offshore-drilling-controversy2.htm |archivedate=2013-04-29 }}</ref>。

[[File:Blacksmoker_in_Atlantic_Ocean.jpg|left]]解放被溶解的[[硫化物|硫化物]]及其他 礦物質在其[[過熱|過熱]]的水噴出。]]大海保存了大量很有價值的溶解礦物<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,871061,00.html | title=Chemistry: Mining the Sea | work=Time | date=1964-05-15 | deadurl=no | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130424120034/http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,871061,00.html | archivedate=2013-04-24 }}</ref>。最重要， [[海盐|海盐]]為了食用及工業用途自史前時代已開始在淺池塘透過陽光蒸發而採集。從土地中過濾而積累起來的[[溴|溴]]在死海成本低廉地回收，蘊量在55,000(ppm)<ref>{{Cite journal | doi = 10.1002/(SICI)1099-1085(200001)14:1<145::AID-HYP916>3.0.CO;2-N| title = The water balance of the Dead Sea: An integrated approach| url = https://archive.org/details/sim_hydrological-processes_2000-01_14_1/page/145| journal = Hydrological Processes| volume = 14| pages = 145–154| year = 2000| last1 = Al-Weshah | first1 = R. A. |bibcode = 2000HyPr...14..145A }}</ref>。其他在海床上或海床內的礦物質可透過[[疏浚|疏浚]]開發。
比起在陸地開採，擁有裝設備可在特定[[造船厂|造船厂]]建造及[[基础设施|基础设施]]成本較低的優點。缺點包括海浪和潮汐做成的問題，挖掘傾向造成淤积，以及{{tsl|en|Spoil tip|弃土堆}}被沖走。有侵蚀海岸和傷害環境的風險<ref>{{cite web |url=http://encyclopedia2.thefreedictionary.com/Undersea+Mining |title=Mining, Undersea |author=Nurok, G. A. |author2=Bubis, I. V. |date=1970–1979 |work=The Great Soviet Encyclopedia, 3rd Edition |access-date=2017-01-03 |archive-date=2013-06-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130605103552/http://encyclopedia2.thefreedictionary.com/undersea+mining |dead-url=no }}</ref> 。{{tsl|en|Seafloor massive sulfide deposits|海底硫化物礦床|硫化物沉积物}}是[[銀|銀]]、[[金|金]]、[[铜|铜]]、[[铅|铅]]、[[锌|锌]]及-{zh-cn:痕量金属;zh-hk:微量金屬}-的潛在來源，只在20世纪60年代才被发现。它們在[[地溫梯度|地溫梯度]] [[过热|过热]]的水從深海熱泉噴射出來時形成，接觸深海的冷水後矿物质沉淀并沉积在噴射口外面。這些礦石質素很高，但目前開採的成本非常高<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.wealthdaily.com/resources/underwater-mining-companies |title=Underwater Mining Companies |author=Kohl, Keith |date=2013 |work=Wealth Daily |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130524121906/http://www.wealthdaily.com/resources/underwater-mining-companies |archivedate=2013-05-24 }}</ref>。在[[巴布亚新几内亚|巴布亚新几内亚]]的海岸已發展使用[[机器人|机器人]]技术進行小規模的深海海底開採，但是障碍重重<ref>{{cite web | url=http://news.nationalgeographic.co.uk/news/2013/13/130201-underwater-mining-gold-precious-metals-oceans-environment/ | title=Will Deep-sea Mining Yield an Underwater Gold Rush? | work=National Geographic | date=2013-02-01 | author=Miner, Meghan | deadurl=no | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130530051935/http://news.nationalgeographic.co.uk/news/2013/13/130201-underwater-mining-gold-precious-metals-oceans-environment | archivedate=2013-05-30 }}</ref>。

[[海水淡化|海水淡化]]是從海水中移除鹽份留下適合[[饮用水|饮用]]與灌溉的清水的技術。海水淡化2個處理方法，[[真空蒸馏|真空蒸馏]]及[[逆滲透|逆滲透]]，並會消耗大量的能量。脱盐一般只在其他水源供應不足或在發電廠產生过量熱能情況下能源充沛下才會使用。生產的副產品盐水包含一些有毒物質，被排出回海裡<ref>{{Cite journal | doi = 10.1016/j.desal.2005.03.095| title = Overview of hybrid desalination systems — current status and future prospects| journal = Desalination| volume = 186| pages = 207–214| year = 2005| last1 = Hamed | first1 = O. A. }}</ref>。

海床上和海洋沉积物內存有大量的[[甲烷水合物|甲烷水合物]]處於大約{{convert|2|°C}}的溫度，這些有利於作為一種潛在的能量來源。一些人估計可用的數量有5百萬立方公里<ref>{{Cite journal | doi = 10.1016/j.earscirev.2003.11.002| title = Global estimates of hydrate-bound gas in marine sediments: How much is really out there?| journal = Earth-Science Reviews| volume = 66| issue = 3–4| pages = 183–197| year = 2004| last1 = Milkov | first1 = A. V. |bibcode = 2004ESRv...66..183M }}</ref>。同時海床上有[[錳結核|錳結核]]，由多層的[[铁|铁]]、[[锰|锰]]及其他在核心的氢氧化物組成。在太平洋這些可能覆蓋多達30%的海海海底。這些礦物在海水中沉淀，並非常緩慢地增長。從中的商業開採[[镍|镍]]在20世纪70年代發明，得因為有更方便的來源而放弃<ref>{{cite journal|journal={{tsl|en|Sedimentary Geology (journal)||Sedimentary Geology}} |volume=217 |issue=1–4 |author1=Achurra, L.E. |author2=Lacassie, J.P. |author3=Le Roux, J.P. |author4=Marquardt, C. |author5=Belmar, M. |author6=Ruiz-del-Solar, J. |author7=Ishman, S.E. |year=2009 |title=Manganese nodules in the Miocene Bahía Inglesa Formation, north-central Chile: Petrography, geochemistry, genesis and palaeoceanographic significance |pages=128–139 |doi=10.1016/j.sedgeo.2009.03.016|bibcode = 2009SedG..217..128A }}</ref>。在適合的地方，[[钻石|钻石]]在海底透過抽吸软管抽取砾石來收集。在更深水的地方則使用流動海底挖掘機，並把沉积物泵送到上方的船只。在纳米比亚現時鑽石從海洋開採比陸上常规方法收集的更多<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mme.gov.na/gsn/diamond.htm |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060406081536/http://www.mme.gov.na/gsn/diamond.htm |archivedate=2006-04-06 |title=Diamonds |date=2006 |work=Geological Survey of Namibia |publisher=Ministry of Mines and Energy }}</ref>。

