===污染===
{{Main article|海洋污染}}

人类活动导致大量物质进入海洋中，燃烧产物通过空气运输并经沉积进入海洋，农业、工业及[[污水处理|污水]]将[[有毒重金屬|重金属]]、[[农药|农药]]、[[多氯聯苯|PCBs]]、[[消毒|消毒剂]]、清洁剂和其他[[化学合成|化学合成]]物通过河流运输进入海洋。这些物质在海洋表面膜和海洋沉积物——特别是在河口泥中聚集，这些污染物所导致的后果其实在很大程度上仍未知因为其涉及的污染物质数量众多并且目前缺乏这些污染物质的生物效应信息<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.seaweb.org/resources/briefings/toxic.php |title=Toxic Pollution |work=Ocean Briefing Book |publisher=SeaWeb |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130613150140/http://www.seaweb.org/resources/briefings/toxic.php |archivedate=2013-06-13 }}</ref>。

重金属主要是[[铜|铜]]、[[铅|铅]]、[[汞|汞]]、[[镉|镉]]和[[锌|锌]]，这些重金属会在海洋无脊椎动物[[生物累积|积累]]然后通过生物链往上层生物传递<ref>{{Cite journal| doi = 10.3923/jas.2004.1.20| bibcode = 2004JApSc...4....1.| url = http://docsdrive.com/pdfs/ansinet/jas/2004/1-20.pdf| title = Heavy Metals in Marine Pollution Perspective–A Mini Review| journal = Journal of Applied Sciences| volume = 4| pages = 1–20| year = 2004| last1 = Ansari| first1 = T. M.| last2 = Marr| first2 = I. L.| last3 = Tariq| first3 = N.| deadurl = no| archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20151222100230/http://docsdrive.com/pdfs/ansinet/jas/2004/1-20.pdf| archivedate = 2015-12-22}}</ref>。

农业地区的[[肥料|肥料]]渗漏是一些地区主要的污染源，未经处理的[[污水处理|污水]]排放也有相似的影响。这些污染源中所含的过多的养分除了会造成土地的[[富营养化|富营养化]]外，因为养分通常是海洋系统的限制因素，所以这些过多的养分也会造成藻类的过渡繁衍（称为[[水华|水华]]或[[藻华|藻华]]）及[[赤潮|赤潮]]，这样会使海水中的含氧量降低以致海洋生物死亡。这种效应已经造成了波罗的海和墨西哥湾的{{tsl|en|Dead_Zone|生态盲区}}<ref name=WWF />。部分水华是由于蓝绿藻（[[藍菌門|蓝细菌]]）造成，这些蓝细菌会使{{tsl|en|Filter_Feeder|滤食性}}贝类带有毒性从而使一些以贝类为主要食物来源的动物——如[[海獭|海獭]]受到伤害<ref name=NationalGeographic>{{cite web |url=http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2012/04/130412-diseases-health-animals-science-environment-oceans/ |title=New Diseases, Toxins Harming Marine Life |author=Dell'Amore, Christine |date=2013-04-12 |work=National Geographic Daily News |publisher=National Geographic |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130422163249/http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2012/04/130412-diseases-health-animals-science-environment-oceans/ |archivedate=2013-04-22 }}</ref>。

核设施同样会造成污染，如爱尔兰海就因{{tsl|en|Sellafield|塞拉菲尔德}}核燃料处理厂造成放射性[[銫-137|銫-137]]污染<ref>{{Cite journal | doi = 10.1016/0025-326X(73)90185-9| title = Distribution of caesium-137 in British coastal waters| url = https://archive.org/details/sim_marine-pollution-bulletin_1973-08_4_8/page/118| journal = Marine Pollution Bulletin| volume = 4| issue = 8| pages = 118–122| year = 1973| last1 = Jefferies | first1 = D. F. | last2 = Preston | first2 = A. | last3 = Steele | first3 = A. K. }}</ref>，另外核事故也会造成放射性物质渗透入海洋——2011年的[[福島第一核電廠|福岛核事故]]<ref>{{Cite journal | doi = 10.1016/j.jenvrad.2011.10.007|pmid=22071362| title = Distribution of oceanic <sup>137</sup>Cs from the Fukushima Dai-ichi Nuclear Power Plant simulated numerically by a regional ocean model| journal = Journal of Environmental Radioactivity| volume = 111| pages = 100–8| year = 2012| last1 = Tsumune | first1 = D. | last2 = Tsubono | first2 = T. | last3 = Aoyama | first3 = M. | last4 = Hirose | first4 = K. }}</ref>。

废物（包括石油、有毒液体、污水和垃圾）向海洋的排放是受[[国际法|国际法]]所规管的，《防止倾倒废弃物及其他物质污染海洋的公约》（简称[[1972伦敦公约|1972伦敦公约]]）是一项为控制废弃物海洋倾倒的[[联合国|联合国]]协议，截至2012年6月8日已有89个国家批准加入该项公约<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.imo.org/OurWork/Environment/SpecialProgrammesAndInitiatives/Pages/London-Convention-and-Protocol.aspx |title=London Convention and Protocol |publisher=International Maritime Organization |access-date=2017-01-03 |archive-date=2012-11-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121106060429/http://www.imo.org/OurWork/Environment/SpecialProgrammesAndInitiatives/Pages/London-Convention-and-Protocol.aspx |dead-url=no }}</ref>。[[防止船舶污染国际公约|防止船舶污染国际公约]]（简称MARPOL 73/78）是国际海事组织为控制海上船只对海洋污染行为的国际公约，截至2013年5月已有152个海洋国家批准加入该项公约<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.imo.org/about/conventions/listofconventions/pages/international-convention-for-the-prevention-of-pollution-from-ships-%28marpol%29.aspx |title=International Convention for the Prevention of Pollution from Ships (MARPOL 73/78) |publisher=International Maritime Organization |access-date=2017-01-03 |archive-date=2012-09-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120919054227/http://www.imo.org/About/Conventions/ListOfConventions/Pages/International-Convention-for-the-Prevention-of-Pollution-from-Ships-(MARPOL).aspx |dead-url=yes }}</ref>。

海洋上大部分的漂浮塑料垃圾并不会进行[[生物降解|生物降解]]，即并不会随着时间分解并最终降解到分子水平，一些刚性塑料可以在海上漂浮多年<ref>{{Cite journal | doi = 10.1098/rstb.2008.0205|pmid=19528051|pmc=2873009| title = Accumulation and fragmentation of plastic debris in global environments| journal = Philosophical Transactions of the Royal Society B: Biological Sciences| volume = 364| issue = 1526| pages = 1985–98| year = 2009| last1 = Barnes | first1 = D. K. A.| last2 = Galgani | first2 = F.| last3 = Thompson | first3 = R. C.| last4 = Barlaz | first4 = M.}}</ref>。在北太平洋环流中部，有一个永久的[[太平洋垃圾帶|太平洋垃圾帶]]累积了大量的漂浮塑料废物<ref>{{Cite journal| doi = 10.1007/s100219900068| jstor = 3658829| url = http://cmore.soest.hawaii.edu/summercourse/2007/documents/Karl_ecosystems.pdf| title = Minireviews: A Sea of Change: Biogeochemical Variability in the North Pacific Subtropical Gyre| year = 1999| last1 = Karl| first1 = D. M.| journal = Ecosystems| volume = 2| issue = 3| pages = 181–214| deadurl = no| archiveurl = http://archive.wikiwix.com/cache/20150831224806/http://cmore.soest.hawaii.edu/summercourse/2007/documents/Karl_ecosystems.pdf| archivedate = 2015-08-31}}</ref>，在北大西洋环流中也有个类似的{{tsl|en|North Atlantic garbage patch|垃圾带}}<ref>{{cite web |author=Lovett, Richard A. |url=http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2010/03/100302-new-ocean-trash-garbage-patch/ |title=Huge Garbage Patch Found in Atlantic too |work=National Geographic |date=2010-03-02 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100305065648/http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2010/03/100302-new-ocean-trash-garbage-patch/ |archivedate=2010-03-05 }}</ref>。一些以海洋为觅食带的海鸟，如[[信天翁|信天翁]]和[[海燕|海燕]]等，常会误将人类产生的污染漂浮物当作食物并在其消化系统中因不能被消化而积聚，最终导致死亡，一些海龟和鲸鱼的胃中也会常发现有[[塑料袋|塑料袋]]和[[鱼线|鱼线]]。而较小的{{tsl|en|Microplastics|微型塑料}}可能会下沉从而危及在海床上的滤食性海洋生物<ref>{{Cite journal | doi = 10.1016/j.envres.2008.07.025|pmid=18949831| title = Synthetic polymers in the marine environment: A rapidly increasing, long-term threat| journal = Environmental Research| volume = 108| issue = 2| pages = 131–9| year = 2008| last1 = Moore | first1 = C. J. |bibcode=2008ER....108..131M}}</ref>。

海洋中大部分的石油污染是来自于城市和工业制造<ref name=WWF>{{cite web |url=http://wwf.panda.org/about_our_earth/blue_planet/problems/pollution/ |title=Marine problems: Pollution |publisher=World Wildlife Fund |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161111022124/http://wwf.panda.org/about_our_earth/blue_planet/problems/pollution/ |archivedate=2016-11-11 }}</ref>。石油污染对海洋生物的危害巨大，油性物质会使海鸟的羽毛阻塞从而降低羽毛的保暖性和隔水性并减少海鸟的浮力，或当海鸟尝试清理羽毛中的油性物质时会被摄入。虽然[[海洋哺乳动物|海洋哺乳动物]]受石油污染影响的程度没有海鸟所受的程度严重，但是它们也会可能因为清理皮毛上的油性物质而使皮毛的保暖性降低造成体温过低，或被这些石油污染物导致失明、脱水或中毒。而当油性物质下沉时，[[底栖生物|底栖无脊椎动物]]会被淹没，鱼类会中毒，海洋生物链会被破坏。短期来说，石油泄漏会导致海洋生物数量减少和种群失衡、人类的休闲活动会受影响、依赖海洋的人的生计被破坏<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nwf.org/What-We-Do/Protect-Habitat/Gulf-Restoration/Oil-Spill/Effects-on-Wildlife.aspx |title=How Does the BP Oil Spill Impact Wildlife and Habitat? |publisher=National Wildlife Federation |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151026032837/http://www.nwf.org/What-We-Do/Protect-Habitat/Gulf-Restoration/Oil-Spill/Effects-on-Wildlife.aspx |archivedate=2015-10-26 }}</ref>。所幸是海洋环境有着自我清洁的特性，清理海洋油污的细菌随着时间的推移自然出现，在墨西哥湾已经出现了以油污为食的细菌，这些细菌只花了几天的时间就把该区域泄漏的油污清理完<ref>{{cite news |title=Gulf of Mexico Has Greater-Than-Believed Ability to Self-Cleanse Oil Spills |author=American Chemical Society |url=http://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2013/04/130408152733.htm |newspaper=Science Daily |date=2013-04-09 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130425090502/http://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2013/04/130408152733.htm |archivedate=2013-04-25 }}</ref>。

=== 海上民族 ===
一些在[[海洋东南亚|海洋东南亚]]的[[遊牧民族|遊牧民族]]土著族群居住在船艇上，並從海裡獲得幾乎所需要的全部東西。[[莫肯人|莫肯人]]位在[[泰国|泰国]]的海岸、[[緬甸|緬甸]]及[[安达曼海|安达曼海]]的島嶼<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.unesco.org/csi/pub/papers2/surin7.htm |title=Environmental, social and cultural settings of the Surin Islands |work=Sustainable Development in Coastal Regions and Small Islands |publisher=UNESCO |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303235713/http://www.unesco.org/csi/pub/papers2/surin7.htm |archivedate=2016-03-03 }}</ref>。[[巴瑶族|巴瑶族]]源自[[苏禄群岛|苏禄群岛]]、[[棉兰老岛|棉兰老岛]]及[[婆罗洲|婆罗洲]]北面<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.everyculture.com/East-Southeast-Asia/Samal-Orientation.html |title=Samal – Orientation |work=Countries and Their Cultures |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141218045839/http://www.everyculture.com/East-Southeast-Asia/Samal-Orientation.html |archivedate=2014-12-18 |accessdate=2017-01-03 }}</ref>。一些[[吉普賽人|吉普賽人]]精於[[自由潛水|自由潛水]]，能夠下潛到{{convert|30|m|sp=us|abbr=on}}水深，然而他們習慣於較安定的陸上生活<ref>{{cite news |title=The last of the sea nomads |author=Langenheim, Johnny |url=https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2010/sep/18/last-sea-nomads |newspaper=The Guardian |date=2010-09-18 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100918085932/http://www.guardian.co.uk/environment/2010/sep/18/last-sea-nomads |archivedate=2010-09-18 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Sea Gypsies of Myanmar |author=Ivanoff, Jacques |url=http://ngm.nationalgeographic.com/2005/04/sea-gypsies/ivanoff-text |newspaper=National Geographic |date=2005-04-01 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131102233125/http://ngm.nationalgeographic.com/2005/04/sea-gypsies/ivanoff-text |archivedate=2013-11-02 }}</ref>。

北极的土着人民，例如[[楚科奇人|楚科奇人]]、[[因纽特人|因纽特人]]、Inuit 原住民族及[[尤皮克人|尤皮克人]]会捕擸海洋哺乳动物，包括[[海豹|海豹]]和[[鲸鱼|鲸鱼]]<ref>{{Cite journal | doi = 10.1890/06-0843.1|jstor= 40062161|pmid=18494367| title = Marine Mammal Harvests and Other Interactions with Humans| journal = Ecological Applications| volume = 18|issue= 2 Suppl| pages = S135–47| year = 2008| last1 = Hovelsrud | first1 = G. K. | last2 = McKenna | first2 = M. | last3 = Huntington | first3 = H. P. }}</ref>。[[托雷斯海峡岛民|托雷斯海峡岛民]]声称拥有[[大堡礁|大堡礁]]的所有权，他们在岛屿上以传统方式生活，包括狩猎，钓鱼，种植和与在附近的[[巴布亚新几内亚|巴布亚新几内亚]]人和[[澳洲|澳洲]]人交易<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gbrmpa.gov.au/our-partners/traditional-owners/traditional-owners-of-the-great-barrier-reef |title=Traditional Owners of the Great Barrier Reef |publisher=Great Barrier Reef Marine Park Authority |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130921060351/http://www.gbrmpa.gov.au/our-partners/traditional-owners/traditional-owners-of-the-great-barrier-reef |archivedate=2013-09-21 }}</ref>。

=== 與大海有關的文化 ===
{{Main article|文化中的海}}

[[File:AssyrianWarship.jpg|thumb]] relief from c. 700 BC showing [[#Animals|fish and a crab]] swimming around a [[雙層槳座戰船|雙層槳座戰船]].]]

在大眾文化中，海的角色是十分矛盾的：既強大又安祥，美麗而又危險<ref name=Stow />{{rp|page=10}}。在神話、宗教、文學、藝術、詩歌、電影、戲劇和音樂中，其都扮演了一定的角色<ref name=Westerdahl>{{Cite journal | doi = 10.1111/j.1095-9270.1994.tb00471.x| title = Maritime cultures and ship types: Brief comments on the significance of maritime archaeology| journal = International Journal of Nautical Archaeology| volume = 23| issue = 4| pages = 265–270| year = 1994| last1 = Westerdahl | first1 = C. }}</ref>。[[古代史|古人]]相信，大海是受到[[水神|水神]]所控制的，故在發生各種與海有關的災難時，需用各種方法使水神的負面情緒平息。不同文化的水神各有不同，例如《[[聖經|聖經]]》中的[[利维坦|利维坦]]<ref>{{cite book |title=The Bible (King James Version) |date=1611 |pages=Job 41: 1–34 |url=http://www.kingjamesbibleonline.org/Job-Chapter-41/ |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130921053332/http://www.kingjamesbibleonline.org/Job-Chapter-41/ |archivedate=2013-09-21 |access-date=2017-01-03 }}</ref>、[[希腊神话|希腊神话]]的[[斯库拉|斯库拉]]<ref>{{cite book | title=The Gods of the Greeks | url=https://archive.org/details/godsofgreeks00kerrich | publisher=Thames and Hudson | author=Kerenyi, C. | date=1974 | pages=[https://archive.org/details/godsofgreeks00kerrich/page/37 37]–40 | isbn=0-500-27048-1}}</ref>、[[日本神話|日本神話]]的[[磯龍捲|磯龍捲]]<ref>{{cite book | title=Ehon Hyaku Monogatari (絵本百物語, "Picture Book of a Hundred Stories") | publisher=Ryûsuiken |language=ja | author=Shunsen, Takehara | date=1841 | location=Kyoto}}</ref>、以及[[北欧神话|北欧神话]]的[[挪威海怪|挪威海怪]]<ref>{{cite book | title=The Naturalist's Library, Volume 8: The Kraken | publisher=W. H. Lizars | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=vwoOAAAAQAAJ&pg=PA327 | author=Pontoppidan, Erich | pages=327–336 | date=1839 | access-date=2017-01-03 | archive-date=2021-03-25 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210325015055/https://books.google.com/books?id=vwoOAAAAQAAJ&pg=PA327 | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=Cotterell>{{cite book |title=World Mythology |url=https://archive.org/details/worldmythology0000unse_u8h4 |editor=Cotterell, Arthur |date=2000 |publisher=Parragon |isbn=978-0-7525-3037-6}}</ref>{{rp|pages=206–208}}。大海亦常見出現於{{link-en|基督教意像|Christian imagery}}中，[[耶穌|耶穌]]的[[使徒_(基督教)|使徒]]當中，就有幾個原在[[加利利海|加利利海]]工作的漁民。

[[File:Great_Wave_off_Kanagawa2.jpg|thumb]]於1829年開始繪畫的《[[神奈川沖浪裏|神奈川沖浪裏]]》，它是《[[冨嶽三十六景|冨嶽三十六景]]》的首景。]]

在藝術此一領域中，人們對大海及與海有關的船隻和生物的描繪多不勝數，從簡單的像法國[[莱塞齐耶德泰阿克-西勒伊|莱塞齐耶德泰阿克-西勒伊]]的洞穴壁畫或早期[[基督教藝術|基督教藝術]]中的[[耶穌魚|耶穌魚]]，以至稍微複雜一點的則有[[荷蘭黃金時代繪畫|荷蘭畫家]]{{link-en|亨德里克·弗鲁姆|Hendrik Cornelisz Vroom}}的作品，甚至複雜得像[[葛饰北斋|葛饰北斋]]的[[浮世繪|浮世繪]]及[[温斯洛·霍默|温斯洛·霍默]]所繪畫的海景。荷兰黄金时期的画家如{{Link-en|扬·波赛利斯|Jan Porcellis}}、{{tsl|en|Hendrick Dubbels|亨德里克·杜博思}}、威廉·范德维德{{tsl|en|Willem van de Velde the Elder|老威廉·范德维德|父}}与{{tsl|en|Willem van de Velde the Elder|小威廉·范德维德|子}}和{{tsl|en|Ludolf Bakhuizen|卢多尔夫·巴克赫伊森}}都曾在他们的作品中赞美过海洋以及军力巅峰时的[[荷蘭皇家海軍|荷兰皇家海军]]。<ref name="Slive">{{cite book|title=Dutch Painting, 1600–1800|url=https://archive.org/details/dutchpainting1600000sliv|date=1995|publisher=Yale University Press|isbn=0-300-07451-4|pages=[https://archive.org/details/dutchpainting1600000sliv/page/213 213]–216|author=Slive, Seymour}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2009/07/31/arts/design/31seascapes.html?_r=0|title=When Galleons Ruled the Waves|date=2009-07-30|publisher=New York Times|author=Johnson, Ken|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160722114631/http://www.nytimes.com/2009/07/31/arts/design/31seascapes.html?_r=0|archivedate=2016-07-22}}</ref>

音乐也从海洋中获得了许多灵感。平静的水面、汹涌的波浪和海上的风暴，这些意象都被水手们吟唱在[[船夫号子|船夫号子]]中，来帮助他们在艰难的任务中协调步调。<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=ULciOFv9dDEC&pg=PR11|title=Poetics of the Elements in the Human Condition: Part I – The Sea: From Elemental Stirrings to the Symbolic Inspiration, Language, and Life-Significance in Literary Interpretation and Theory|date=1985|publisher=Springer|isbn=978-90-277-1906-5|pages=4–8|editor=Tymieniecka, Anna–Teresa}}</ref>与海相关的古典音乐有[[理查德·瓦格纳|理查德·瓦格纳]]的《[[漂泊的荷蘭人_(歌劇)|漂泊的荷蘭人]]》<ref>{{cite web | url=http://users.belgacom.net/wagnerlibrary/prose/wagauto.htm | title=An Autobiographical Sketch | publisher=The Wagner Library | date=1843 | author=Wagner, Richard | deadurl=no | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130511142319/http://users.belgacom.net/wagnerlibrary/prose/wagauto.htm | archivedate=2013-05-11 }}</ref>、[[阿希尔-克洛德·德彪西|克洛德·德彪西]]的《{{tsl|en|La mer (Debussy)|海 (德布西)|海}}》（1903-1905年）<ref>{{cite encyclopedia | chapter=Debussy and Nature | title=The Cambridge Companion to Debussy | series = Cambridge Companions to Music| publisher=Cambridge University Press | editor=Potter, Caroline | editor2=Trezise, Simon | date=1994 | page=149 |isbn=0-521-65478-5}}</ref>、[[查尔斯·维利尔斯·斯坦福|查尔斯·维利尔斯·斯坦福]]的《海洋之歌》（1904年）和《艦隊之歌》（1910年）、[[爱德华·埃尔加|爱德华·埃尔加]]的《{{tsl|en|Sea Pictures|海景}}》（1899年）及[[雷夫·佛漢·威廉斯|雷夫·佛漢·威廉斯]]的《{{tsl|en|A Sea Symphony|海之交響曲}}》（1903-1909年）<ref>{{cite book |title=The Symphonies of Ralph Vaughan Williams |url=https://archive.org/details/symphoniesofralp00schw |last=Schwartz |first=Elliot S. |date=1964 |publisher=University of Massachusetts Press |asin=B0007DESPS }}</ref>。

[[File:Winslow_Homer_-_The_Gulf_Stream_-_Metropolitan_Museum_of_Art.jpg|thumb]].]]

海，作为一个象征，几个世纪以来一直在文学和诗歌中反复出现。有时，它只是一个切入背景，而且总会引入像风暴、海难、战斗、苦难、灾难、希望的曙光亦或是死亡<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=ULciOFv9dDEC&pg=PR45|title=Poetics of the Elements in the Human Condition: Part I – The Sea: From Elemental Stirrings to the Symbolic Inspiration, Language, and Life-Significance in Literary Interpretation and Theory|date=1985|publisher=Springer|isbn=978-90-277-1906-5|page=45|editor=Tymieniecka, Anna–Teresa}}</ref>。在写于公元前8世纪的[[史诗|史诗]]《[[奥德赛|奥德赛]]》中<ref name="Odyssey">{{cite book|title=The Odyssey|url=https://archive.org/details/odyssey00home_4|date=2003|publisher=Penguin|others=Translation by Rieu, D. C. H.|isbn=0-14-044911-6|pages=xi|author=Homer}}</ref>，[[荷马|荷马]]描述了希腊英雄[[奥德修斯|奥德修斯]]在《[[伊利亚特|伊利亚特]]》中的战争结束后十年艰苦的返乡航程中所经历的诸多劫难<ref>{{cite web|url=http://homepage.usask.ca/~jrp638/CourseNotes/OdSummary.html|title=Plot Outline for Homer's Odyssey|author=Porter, John|date=2006-05-08|publisher=University of Saskatchewan|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121022012733/http://homepage.usask.ca/~jrp638/CourseNotes/OdSummary.html|archivedate=2012-10-22}}</ref>。在日本诗人[[松尾芭蕉|松尾芭蕉]]（1644–1694）的[[俳句|俳句]]诗歌中，海也是一个反复出现的主题<ref>{{cite web | url=http://thegreenleaf.co.uk/hp/basho/00bashohaiku.htm | title=A Selection of Matsuo Basho's Haiku | publisher=Greenleaf | author=Basho, Matsuo | access-date=2017-01-03 | archive-date=2013-05-18 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130518030554/http://thegreenleaf.co.uk/hp/basho/00bashohaiku.htm | dead-url=no }}</ref>。在现代文学中，像[[赫尔曼·梅尔维尔|赫尔曼·梅尔维尔]]<ref>{{cite book | url=http://www.bartleby.com/187/5.html | chapter=Chapter 3. Romances of Adventure. Section 2. Herman Melville | author=Van Doren, Carl | title=The American Novel | date=1921 | publisher=Bartleby.com | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130902092546/http://www.bartleby.com/187/5.html | archivedate=2013-09-02 | access-date=2017-01-03 }}</ref>、{{tsl|en|Joseph Conrad's career at sea|約瑟夫·康拉德的海上生涯|約瑟夫·康拉德}}<ref>{{cite book | title=Joseph Conrad: A Life|isbn=157113347X | publisher=Camden House | author=Najder, Zdzisław | date=2007 | page=187 }}</ref>及[[赫尔曼·沃克|赫尔曼·沃克]]这样的海员也创作过许多受海启发的小说<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pprize.com/BookDetail.php/34|title=The Caine Mutiny|date=2006|publisher=Pulitzer Prize First Edition Guide|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130921054650/http://www.pprize.com/BookDetail.php/34|archivedate=2013-09-21}}</ref>。[[精神病学|精神病学]]家[[卡尔·荣格|卡尔·荣格]]认为，在[[释梦|释梦]]的时候，海象征着[[潛意識|个人]]和[[集体潜意识|集体无意识]]<ref name="Jung">{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=SWvdQyo_ZX0C&pg=PA122|title=Dreams|date=1985|publisher=Ark Paperbacks|others=Translated by Hull, R.F.C|isbn=978-0-7448-0032-6|pages=122, 192|author=Jung, Carl Gustav}}</ref>。尽管地球上生命的起源仍然是个争论中的问题<ref>{{Cite journal | doi = 10.1007/s10509-008-9876-6| title = Origin of Life| journal = Astrophysics and Space Science| volume = 317| issue = 3–4| pages = 267–278| year = 2008| last1 = Lal | first1 = A. K. |arxiv = 0907.3552 |bibcode = 2008Ap&SS.317..267L }}</ref>，自然学家[[雷切尔·卡森|雷切尔·卡森]]却还是在《{{tsl|en|The Sea Around Us|我們周圍的海洋}}》中写道：“生命的源头是海洋，它孕育了种种生物，现在却被其中一种生物的活动所威胁，这是多么奇怪的情形啊。不过，虽然海洋环境不断恶化，但是这片无边的大洋仍然会继续存在下去，实际上，生物本身才是真正的受害者。”<ref name="winchester">{{cite book|last=Winchester|first=Simon|title=Atlantic: A vast ocean of a million stories|url=https://archive.org/details/atlanticvastocea0000winc|publisher=Harper Press|location=London|date=2010|pages=[https://archive.org/details/atlanticvastocea0000winc/page/354 354]–356|isbn=978-0-00-736459-6}}</ref>

